what:
where:
Abu Dhabi
This is an excellent opportunity to join a prestigious Government hospital with a strong clinical and academic reputation. The hospital, which is a tertiary care centre, seeks to recruit an outstanding Consultant Plastic Surgeonwho can develop the existing service. The position attracts a very attractive salary package which is tax free.
Key Performance Criteria:
Develop clinically sound Plastic and Reconstructive Surgical service within JCI clinical governance frameworks Educate and supervise medical students, residents and Specialists Undertake clinical research and audit
Essential Qualifications and Experience
Residency or other recognised structured postgraduate training programme in Plastic Surgery in a country recognised by HAAD in Tier 1 (UK, Ireland, USA, Canada, South Africa, Germany , Austria, Switzerland, France, Belgium, Australia, New Zealand) Appropriate Board Certification or Fellowship for the HAAD Consultant License (see attached document). Qualifications listed as Tier 1 only are accepted. Minimum 2 years experience as a Consultant or Attending physician after Board Certification or Specialist Registration. Excellent spoken and written English Knowledge of Arabic desirable
To apply, please send a detailed CV with full employment history and a description of scope of practice.
